06/07/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Authorities have confirmed the first two cases of the H1N1 virus, popularly known as swine flu, in the country, Health Minister Bujar Osmani told a press conference in Skopje on Saturday (July 4th). 
One of the patients is still in hospital in stable condition. 
The other has recovered and is back home. 
(Makfax, MIA, Xinhua - 05/07/09)
